Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine cereal and milk. Let stand about 2 minutes or until cereal softens. Add egg and shortening. Beat well. Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined. Portion batter evenly into twelve greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups coated with cooking spray. Bake in oven at 200 degrees C (400 degrees F) for about 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown. Serve warm.